com.betfair.cougar.transport.activemq

Class ActiveMQEventTransportImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.betfair.cougar.core.api.transports.AbstractRegisterableTransport
      • com.betfair.cougar.transport.jms.JmsEventTransportImpl
        • com.betfair.cougar.transport.activemq.ActiveMQEventTransportImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.betfair.cougar.core.api.BindingDescriptorRegistrationListener, com.betfair.cougar.core.api.transports.EventTransport, org.springframework.beans.factory.Aware, org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean, org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware

    public class ActiveMQEventTransportImpl
extends JmsEventTransportImpl
    This class implements an ActiveMQ JMS based transport implementation. The implementation contains a set of defaults for a Sonic transport that are overrideable through spring config if you'd like to do something different

      • setSequential

        public void setSequential(boolean sequential)
        Sonic Sequential connection set searching: If true, starts attempting to connect to the first broker in the list; if false, starts attempting to connect to a random element in the list. After that, tries to connect to each broker in sequence until a successful connect occurs, or the list is exhausted.
        Parameters:
        sequential - - if true, start with the first broker in the list, if false choose one randomly
